	+ Fixed size at compile time.
	+ More efficient in terms of memory usage.
	+ Provides additional functionality like bit manipulation operations.
	+ Better for when you know the size of the bitset at compile time and don't need to change it.
* `std::vector<bool>`:
	+ Dynamic size, can change at runtime.
	+ Less efficient in terms of memory usage due to overhead.
	+ Provides functionality common to other vector types.
	+ Better for when you need a dynamic size or want to use vector functionality.

